OL,3,CSoldier reflects on surviving knife
OL,4,Cattack metres from family home
OL,6,FAn army officer who was brutally
OL,7,Fattacked by a man in the street as he
OL,8,Fwalked home says he feels "lucky to be
OL,9,Falive."
OL,11,FLieutenant Colonel Mark Teeton was
OL,12,Fstabbed repeatedly by Anthony Esan in
OL,13,FSally Port Gardens, near Brompton
OL,14,FBarracks, in Chatham, on July 23 2024.
OL,16,FOn Friday, Esan was sentenced to life
OL,17,Fimprisonment with a minimum term of
OL,18,Fseven years and detained at Broadmoor
OL,19,FHospital, in Berkshire, indefinitely.
