OL,4,Cattack metres from family home
OL,6,FLieutenant Colonel Teeton described it
OL,7,Fas "a pretty routine day at work",
OL,8,Fvolunteering with the Institution of
OL,9,FCivil Engineers on the day of the
OL,10,Fattack, before he walked his normal
OL,11,Ffive minute route home.
OL,13,FTouching on the moment he was attacked
OL,14,Fby Anthony Esan, he said: "I was
OL,15,Fshouting out to police.
OL,17,F"As well as Eileen, coming out and
OL,18,Fconfronting the attacker, there were
OL,19,Fothers who, heard my shouts and came
OL,20,Fout and see what was going on.
