OL,3,CSoldier reflects on surviving knife
OL,4,Cattack metres from family home
OL,6,F"Looking back, there is so many little
OL,7,Fthings I remember from during the
OL,8,Finitial shout to seek help," Mark
OL,9,Fadded.
OL,11,F"The paramedic, to those intervening
OL,12,Fto, curtail the attack, and then the
OL,13,Fthe ambulance and the paramedics
OL,14,Farriving and others doing first aid on
OL,15,Fmyself."
OL,17,FMark was rushed to hospital where he
OL,18,Fremained in and out of consciousness
OL,19,Ffor several days whilst he was
OL,20,Fundergoing multiple surgeries.
