OL,3,CSoldier reflects on surviving knife
OL,4,Cattack metres from family home
OL,6,F"It was five weeks of physical
OL,7,Ftraining every day, and you're around
OL,8,Fother people who've had horrific
OL,9,Finjuries, and I think that collective
OL,10,Fof just being able to talk to other
OL,11,Fpeople in similar situations or even
OL,12,Fworse situations than I've found
OL,13,Fmyself in - it helps you."
OL,15,FMark's recovery has been so successful
OL,16,Fthat he managed to complete the
OL,17,FManchester Half Marathon in October
OL,18,Flast year, and he's even lined up
OL,19,Fanother race over the next few months.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G9/11
